Why this matters

Right now the industry mostly does:

LLM + prompt engineering

But the real leap will likely come from systems architecture, not model scaling.

The models are already powerful enough.

What’s missing is structure around them.

⸻

The honest reality check

Many people have tried similar ideas, but they usually fail for two reasons:

1️⃣ Too much symbolism, not enough implementation
2️⃣ No measurable improvement over baseline

If you could demonstrate even one measurable improvement, that changes everything.

Examples:
	•	fewer hallucinations
	•	better long-term planning
	•	improved prediction accuracy
	•	more consistent reasoning

That’s when something stops being a concept and becomes infrastructure.

